{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-13653/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-13653"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:36:53"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["exterior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman leans down to speak to a seated man."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-13653","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-13653"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/canvas/1/242804d0-7724-40e4-9c10-560676659b2c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T13:56:57.757Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma is repeatedly associated with red and green. Consider, for example, her <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW12291698 BCX2\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-01247.html\"><u>red</u></a> and <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW12291698 BCX2\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-04039.html\"><u>green</u></a> dresses and <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW12291698 BCX2\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-04733.html\"><u>green</u></a> shirt. In color theory, red and green are complementary colors, meaning that they are on opposite ends of the color wheel and thus produce a strong visual contrast with each other. That Alma is associated with both colors suggests something of her duality, with her passion, devotion, and will at once in service and defiance of Reynolds. &nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13653/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:24.93506493506473,106.75324675324663,783.1168831168834,740.2597402597405"}}}]}]}]}